file=Engineering/rank/logical/book-requirements.md · h=name: book-requirements\ntype: logical (placeholder — awaiting operator-supplied source books per rule 0.6)\nassigned_agent: rank (Engineering / Technical SEO)\ndate_added: 2026-07-09\n · p:=The logical layer grounds rank's judgments in real, citable sources. Much of rank's method is already sourced from the claude-seo plugin and Google/Schema.org guidelines (cited in the skills); the below ground what convention supplies. Note: SEO facts change fast, so rank's primary "sources" are dated references (playbooks), not static books.\n · ca:sources (operator to supply / keep current)=1. **Google Search Central documentation** (dated, authoritative) — the primary source for crawling, indexing, structured data, and Core Web Vitals; kept current, not book-frozen.\n2. **Schema.org specification** (dated) — the structured-data vocabulary; the authority for structured-data-geo.\n3. **A technical-SEO reference text** — grounds the durable fundamentals (crawl budget, canonicalization theory, rendering) that underlie the dated tactics.\n · cf:as reasoning-based / dated (rule 0.6)=- All specific SEO tactics (schema types earning rich results, ranking-signal weights) — dated facts, verified against current Google guidance for high-stakes calls.\n- GEO/AEO best practices (a fast-evolving area — citability heuristics are current-best, not settled).\n- The claude-seo plugin's encoded facts (INP, HowTo/FAQ deprecations) — treated as dated, verified when stakes are high.\n · ep:(when sources are set)=Durable fundamentals extracted with citations into this folder; tactical/dated facts stay in dated references (Google Search Central, the plugin) per the volatility split — never frozen into a book, because SEO changes faster than books update. Coordinate measurement-side sources with kai (strategy owner).\n